</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B36F96F75FF9C0DA9FCB9FD70FC05" blockId="3.[190,1399,838,936]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
The subgenus currently contains 4 species, but an undescribed species from 
<collectingRegion id="49F0F81B6F75FF9C0927FCB9FB7BFCC2" box="[1072,1157,838,864]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Hainan</collectingRegion>
Island (Wuzhishan), illustrated and erroneously referred to as 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D7A6F75FF9C0FBFFC95FC85FC26" authorityName="Che, Zhang &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2007" box="[680,891,874,900]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Gergithus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multipunctatus">
<emphasis id="B940EAEB6F75FF9C0FBFFC95FC85FC26" box="[680,891,874,900]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">G. multipunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in both 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B086F75FF9C0EF6FC96FB17FC26" author="Chen X. - S. &amp; Zhang Z. - G. &amp; Chang Z." box="[993,1257,873,900]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refId="ref6215" refString="Chen X. - S., Zhang Z. - G. &amp; Chang Z. 2014. Issidae and Caliscelidae from China. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang." type="book" year="2014">
Chen 
<emphasis id="B940EAEB6F75FF9C093FFC95FB9AFC26" box="[1064,1124,874,900]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
(2014: 56)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B086F75FF9C0832FC95FEAAFC0A" author="Guo M. &amp; Chen X. - S." pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="429 - 434" refId="ref6477" refString="Guo M. &amp; Chen X. - S. 2015. Morphological comparison on six male Gergithus (Fulgoroidea, Issidae) from China. Sichuan Journal of Zoology 34 (3): 429 - 434." type="journal article" year="2015">Guo &amp; Chen (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, also belongs to the group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B36F96F75FF9C0DA9FC31FD45FBAE" blockId="3.[190,1399,974,1036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Pending additional new groupings (see discussion), all other species are currently retained in the nominal subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D7A6F75FF9C0C25FC0EFD49FBAE" authority="(Gergithus) Stal, 1870" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1870" box="[306,695,1009,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Gergithus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Gergithus">
<emphasis id="B940EAEB6F75FF9C0C25FC0EFDC8FBA9" box="[306,566,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Gergithus (Gergithus)</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B086F75FF9C0F2AFC0EFD49FBAE" author="Stal C." box="[573,695,1009,1036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="607 - 756" refId="ref6780" refString="Stal C. 1870. Hemiptera insularum Philippinarum. - Bidrag till Philippinska oarnes Hemipterfauna. Ofversigt af Kongliga Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar 27: 607 - 756. http: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 24634225" type="journal article" year="1870">Stål, 1870</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
